should i take this blind dog someone is offering me a blind dog because they already have three dogs and need to find him a home this puppy was born blind could there be other medical problems i would need to worry about is taking care of a blind dog a lot more difficult than a dog with sight the dog is really cute and i would like to care for him any advice my first foster dog was blind and deaf i was amazed at how well he got around he was the sweetest most wonderful dog i would highly recommend you take him there could be other medical problems but usually there aren't however if you really wanted to you could take him to a vet and see if there's anything that can be done to restore his sight before you take him take the dog to a vet and have him checked out the vet will tell you why he's blind and if there's anything that can be done about it you will be able to ask any questions you have about his health etc usually vet visits are with a blind dog at first you have to let him get used to your house even if he's housetrained he might have some accidents at first he has to learn where things are but after he settles in i guarantee you'll forget he's blind sometimes Dog Aphasia Hearing impairment Medicine Marilyn Monroe Pet skunk Dog training Housebreaking Garfield Brian Griffin Veterinarian Milton H. Erickson Breastfeeding Fancy rat Shaggy dog story Team Fortress Classic Non-Hodgkin's lymphoma Guinea pig Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Crate training Docking Diabetes mellitus Labrador Retriever Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Prostate cancer Hamster Obedience training Beethoven (film) Ludwig Wittgenstein Childbirth Blood (computer game) Humphrey Bogart Avenue Q Mixed-breed dog Great Dane Retinol Havanese Shetland Sheepdog Color blindness Puppy mill Philip Stanhope, 4th Earl of Chesterfield Autism Juliana of the Netherlands Social rule Rabies Piccolo Junior Saga Microchip implant (animal) One Tree Hill (TV series) Ferret Cat Education in the United State